
  <sn><md>### Standard External CSS Link

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to.css" type="text/css">
```

**Description:**
The standard practice is to place CSS `<link>` tags **inside the head** section of your HTML document.
This ensures that the CSS is loaded **before** the page content is displayed, preventing a flash of unstyled content (FOUC).

In HTML5, the `type` attribute is **optional**, since browsers automatically recognize the stylesheet as CSS.

**Example (HTML5 standard):**

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to.css">
```

and

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to.css" type="text/css">
```

Both have the same effect in HTML5.
