<sn><md>### Using `@import` Inside a `<style>` Tag

Another (less common) way to include an external stylesheet is with the `@import` rule inside a `<style>` element.

**Example (with type attribute):**

```html
<style type="text/css">
  @import("path/to.css");
</style>
```

**Example (HTML5 version):**

```html
<style>
  @import("path/to.css");
</style>
```

**Note:**
Using `@import` is generally discouraged because it loads CSS **after** the main stylesheet, which can slow down page rendering compared to using `<link>`.
